<br>
When you don't work with a reference you remember all of the basic shapes, but I think you forget what's underneath them.  I think the key to working on anatomy without a reference is remembering what's under the skin.  for example, the collar bone lines that you have near the neck would be a little lower, and that lines moves up and then forms the shoulders.  in the chest area you have of course the ribs, and on top of that you have the breasts.  A rule of thumb that I read for the breasts is that the nipples are at a 90 degree angle from the center of the collar bone.  Not to say you need to be getting out your protractor or anything, but just as a general reference.  <br>
<br>
I think you've got all of the concepts down, you just need to work a little on proportions.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It's a great start!<br>
<br>
Thx<br>
<br>
Mari <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mysticmari.com/marisig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kempokatt>kempokatt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/4/03 10:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9841.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kempokatt.250free.com/images/avat1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drawing of a girl - Basics</span><hr size=1> I agree with Mari...<br>
<br>
Drawing from pure memory is not a good idea (Unless you're a certified genius).<br>
<br>
Here's some things you can try....<br>
<br>
Get a $5.00 dollar (US) art manikin. They are easy to use, cheap, and will help you to visualize forms in 3D.<br>
<br>
You can get them here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.dickblick.com/zz216/01/products.asp?param=0&ig_id=2949">www.dickblick.com/zz216/0...ig_id=2949</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The 12&quot; model is UNDER 5 bucks (must add shipping though) or go to your local art supply store. I'm lucky because I live close to several colleges so there are many art stores close to me.<br>
<br>
-------------------<br>
Do a &quot;stick figure&quot; skeleton and flesh it out.<br>
<br>
-------------<br>
Get a friend to pose, take pictures of friends in poses or use SOME sort of reference (The Mona Lisa wasn't painted from memory!)<br>
<br>
That's it from me - FOR NOW!<br>
