 of the kings of comic art (in my opinion). <br>
<br>
You can check some of his art at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.joemadfan.com" target="top">www.joemadfan.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
One thing that never fails: KEEP PRACTICING! One can never find a shortcut around this, and investment is key. You'll have great fun along hte way. <br>
<br>
If you mean keeping the image in your head, it helps to focus on the details, at least for me, and the stance. Thats all I really need, from there on out, I can use the stance to create a character that may or may not look like the one I imagined, but with the kick-ass details in mind, it really doesnt matter.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rexsyn>Rexsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mindlesscartoons.o-f.com/mypic.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/8/03 6:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9841.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drawing of a girl - Basics</span><hr size=1> I agree to the ones who have commented before me and would like to add that you should draw the character doing something, instead of just standing there dead as a doornail. This will add some interest to your art. I began drawing things like that, a character that has no motion or life in it. What helps me is to draw an action line first then curve the spine along with it. That was the most important concept that I had been taught to by a book. Other than that practice, practice, practice... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rexsyn>Rexsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mindlesscartoons.o-f.com/mypic.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/10/03 12:41 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=9841.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=9841